title: Architects on architecture; new directions in America (Art Book)
description:
Walker | 1966 | Pdf | English | ISBN10 080270641X | 415 pag | 71.1 MB

This book presents the design approach, the ideas and the major work of some forty leading American architects or groups of architects. The architects were not selected to represent a preconceived point of view, but because their buildings, their statements and their concerns seem generally to represent the most positive and influential directions in American architecture today. Their approaches are diverse, ranging from the more rational, structural, to the more plastic, sculptural, while certain consistencies also indicate parallel ideas in general directions
